## 🐛 KNOWN ISSUES

| ID | Status | Description | Workaround | Root cause |
|----|--------|-------------|-----------|------------|
| 001 | `open` | `wmic` deprecated in Win11 22H2+ may fail in future builds | Script still works in 22H2/23H2/24H2 as of 2026-06 | Microsoft deprecating WBEM CLI |
| 002 | `open` | Space diff calculation truncates numbers with `!VAR:~0,9!` — inaccurate on drives > 1 TB | Cosmetic only; does not affect cleaning | Batch integer overflow with >10-digit numbers |
| 003 | `open` | `wsreset.exe` opens a Store window briefly | Window closes automatically | wsreset design |

### Tech debt
- Migrate `wmic` queries to `Get-CimInstance` wrapped in `powershell -Command` for long-term Win11 compatibility.
- Space diff math should use PowerShell integer arithmetic instead of Batch set /a with truncation.

