## 🗒 AI NOTES

_Newest entries first._

2026-06-12 — The DISM source detection loop iterates ALL 26 drive letters (A-Z). This is intentional — users mount ISOs on unpredictable letters (sometimes Z:, sometimes D:). The loop takes milliseconds even with 26 iterations since most `if exist` checks fail fast on non-existent paths.

2026-06-12 — `setlocal enabledelayedexpansion` is critical for the DISM source detection. Without it, `!BEST_SOURCE!` inside the `for` loop would expand to empty string. Never remove this from line 2 of the script.

2026-06-12 — The `wmic os get localdatetime` for the log timestamp returns a 14-character string like `20260612153045`. The `%DT:~0,8%_%DT:~8,6%` syntax slices it to `20260612_153045`. This is locale-independent — unlike `%DATE%` which varies by Windows region settings.

2026-06-12 — `DISM /StartComponentCleanup /ResetBase` is irreversible. It removes the ability to uninstall Windows updates. This was a deliberate v2.0 decision to maximize space recovery. Do not make this optional without a clear user warning.

2026-06-12 — The `explorer.exe` kill + restart in step 5 of FASE 1 is needed to unlock `thumbcache_*.db` files. Without it, the delete silently fails. The Explorer restart is fast but may briefly flash the desktop.

